Let E be the expected value of the winnings from a single coin flip.

E = P(heads) * Winnings(heads) + P(tails) * Winnings(tails) + P(edge) * Winnings(edge)
E = \left(\frac{1}{2}\right)\left(1\right) + \left(\frac{1}{3}\right)\left(3\right) + \left(\frac{1}{6}\right)\left(-5\right).
E = \frac{1}{2}+\frac{3}{3}-\frac{5}{6}
E = \frac{1}{2}+\frac{3}{3}-\frac{5}{6}
E = \frac{3}{6} + \frac{4}{6} - \frac{5}{6}
E = \frac{3}{6} + \frac{4}{6} - \frac{5}{6} 
E = \frac{2}{6}
E = \frac{2}{6} = \frac{1}{3}
E = \frac{2}{6} = \frac{1}{3}
